<subSubSection pageId="157" pageNumber="158" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="157.[151,1437,447,1084]" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,988,1012]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="158" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is another very common intertidal crab, often found under rocks in rubble beds in the midlittoral zone. In life, pereopods 5 are folded alongside the carapace. Records of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Randall" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1083,1210,1024,1048]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="157" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinctipes">
<emphasis box="[1083,1097,1025,1048]" italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1111,1210,1024,1047]" italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">cinctipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from south of Point Conception prior to 1945 are likely to be misidentifications of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Glassell" authorityYear="1945" box="[852,976,1060,1084]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="157" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cabrilloi">
<emphasis box="[852,866,1061,1084]" italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[880,976,1060,1084]" italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">cabrilloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
